-A browser extension that enhances [prompts.chat](https://prompts.chat) with additional features and improvements. This extension is built on top of the amazing [Awesome ChatGPT Prompts](https://github.com/f/awesome-chatgpt-prompts) collection by [Fatih Kadir Akın](https://github.com/f).
+This is **Minsky**, a white-label fork of the [prompts.chat browser extension](https://github.com/fatihsolhan/prompts-chat-extension)
+for the internal use of PGE-PI. It connects to the private Minsky prompt library at
+`minsky.pge.pi.gov.br` instead of the public prompts.chat — see
+[**Connecting to Minsky**](#connecting-to-minsky) below.
+
+## Upstream-sync-safe customizations
+
+Every change from upstream lives in `patches/*.patch` and is reapplied automatically on
+`yarn install` (via `postinstall`, see `scripts/apply-patches.sh`) — source files stay
+byte-for-byte identical to upstream in git. To add a new customization: edit the file, run
+`git diff <file> > patches/000N-description.patch` (add `--binary` for icons/images), then
+`git checkout -- <file>` to keep the working tree pristine.
+
+## Connecting to Minsky
+
+Unlike upstream, this extension requires an **API key** — Minsky's prompt library is private
+(login-gated), so the extension can't browse it anonymously. Click the key icon in the toolbar
+and follow the in-app instructions to generate one from your Minsky account settings.
 
